# Web3Forms access key for the contact form.
#
# This is a PUBLIC client key (it can only submit the form and email you) — it is
# not a secret in the traditional sense, but we keep it out of source control as
# good practice. On a static site the value still ends up in the shipped JS.
#
# Local development:
#   1. Copy this file to ".env.local"  (".env.local" is git-ignored)
#   2. Put your real key after the "=" below.
#
# Production (GitHub Pages):
#   Add a repo secret named VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY (Settings → Secrets and
#   variables → Actions). The deploy workflow injects it at build time.

VITE_WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your-web3forms-access-key
